  "font": {
    "plain": {
      "$value": "Plain",
      "$type": "fontFamily",
      "$description": "All roles — display, headings, body, caption, nav, button. The single typeface carries the entire site. Weight contrast is limited (400 vs 500) so hierarchy comes from size and tracking, not boldness. The 52px display at -0.02em tracking is anti-display: it whispers instead of shouts. Line-heights under 1.1 on 32–52px create stacked, compressed blocks where headings read as solid slabs. Open features 'kern' and 'case' hint at a typeface with carefully spaced uppercase alternates — the 'case' feature likely gives access to stylistic capital forms."
    }
  },
